	rid of eslint warnings.

2017-10-11  Björn Ricks <bjoern.ricks@greenbone.net>

	* src/html/classic/ng/src/web/pages/targets/detailspage.js,
	src/html/classic/ng/src/web/pages/targets/listpage.js: Use TargetComponent
	directly instead of withTargetComponent HOC in target list and details page.
	It's easier to understand what's going on with the render props pattern
	then with a HOC.

2017-10-11  Björn Ricks <bjoern.ricks@greenbone.net>

	* src/html/classic/ng/src/web/pages/targets/withTargetComponent.js: Refactor
	withTargetCompent HOC to use TargetComponent. TargetComponent also got
	extracted from withTargetComponent before but uses render props pattern.

2017-10-11  Björn Ricks <bjoern.ricks@greenbone.net>

	* src/html/classic/ng/src/web/pages/targets/component.js: Don't add a generic
	onError handler to TargetComponent. Using this handler may have resulted in
	issues while saving and creating targets. In this cases errors should be
	handled by the dialogs which wouldn't be possibe if onError is set.

2017-10-11  Björn Ricks <bjoern.ricks@greenbone.net>

	* src/html/classic/ng/src/web/entities/page.js: Remove onFilterCreateClick
	from EntitiesPage. This handler wasn't ever used and now also is removed from
	Powerfilter component. Require other handlers of EntitiesPage.

2017-10-11  Björn Ricks <bjoern.ricks@greenbone.net>

	* src/html/classic/ng/src/web/entity/withEntityComponent.js,
	src/html/classic/ng/src/web/pages/hosts/withHostComponent.js,
	src/html/classic/ng/src/web/pages/notes/withNoteComponent.js,
	src/html/classic/ng/src/web/pages/os/detailspage.js,
	src/html/classic/ng/src/web/pages/overrides/withOverrideComponent.js,
	src/html/classic/ng/src/web/pages/permissions/withPermissionsComponent.js,
	src/html/classic/ng/src/web/pages/tasks/withTaskComponent.js: Refactor
	withEntityComponent to use EntityComponent. EntityComponent got extracted from
	withEntityComponent before but has slighly different semantics. Action
	handlers for CRUD operations are now called xyz (e.g. clone) instead of onXyz
	(e.g. onClone). Also EntityComponent uses render props. It's now clearer which
	handlers are input props for EntityComponent and which handlers are created by
	EntityComponent and passed to its child.

2017-10-11  Björn Ricks <bjoern.ricks@greenbone.net>

	* src/html/classic/ng/src/web/entity/container.js: Convert EntityContainer to
	user render prop pattern.

