	* src/html/classic/ng/src/gmp/models/report/parser.js: Set a unique id on
	error message objects. The unique id is required for rendering dynamic lists
	in react.

2017-10-11  Björn Ricks <bjoern.ricks@greenbone.net>

	* src/html/classic/ng/src/web/pages/reports/errorstable.js,
	src/html/classic/ng/src/web/pages/reports/sort.js: Only render html anchors if
	links prop is set. This allows using the error messages table also in the
	gsr-html report. Add hostname column to the table. And only render link to
	host if we have an asset id.

2017-10-11  Björn Ricks <bjoern.ricks@greenbone.net>

	* src/html/classic/ng/src/gmp/models/report/parser.js: Fix parsing of error
	message hosts.

2017-10-10  Björn Ricks <bjoern.ricks@greenbone.net>

	* src/html/classic/ng/src/web/pages/hosts/identifiers.js,
	src/html/classic/ng/src/web/pages/results/detailspage.js,
	src/html/classic/ng/src/web/pages/tasks/detailspage.js: Link to ng report
	details page.

2017-10-10  Björn Ricks <bjoern.ricks@greenbone.net>

	* src/html/classic/ng/.env,
	src/html/classic/ng/package.json: Revert r29797. The nodejs debian package
	from https://deb.nodesource.com installs a /etc/profile.d/nodejs.sh file. This
	file gets sourced when starting a new interactive bash shell. In this file a
	NODE_PATH environment variable is already set. If a environment variable is
	already set it doesn't get overridden by the one from the .env file. This
	causes a bug while building ng because the gmp js module can't be found.
	Therefore override the NODE_PATH variable when running yarn (or npm) build via
	package.json.

2017-10-09  Björn Ricks <bjoern.ricks@greenbone.net>

	* src/html/classic/ng/src/web/components/dashboard/dashboard.js: Code cleanup
	to satisfy eslint.

2017-10-09  Björn Ricks <bjoern.ricks@greenbone.net>

	* src/html/classic/ng/src/web/pages/page.js: Remove capabilities child context
	type from Page component. This is obsolete since Page uses the
	CapabiltitiesProvider component.

