	src/html/classic/ng/src/gmp/models/override.js,
	src/html/classic/ng/src/gmp/models/permission.js,
	src/html/classic/ng/src/gmp/models/portlist.js,
	src/html/classic/ng/src/gmp/models/report.js,
	src/html/classic/ng/src/gmp/models/reportformat.js,
	src/html/classic/ng/src/gmp/models/result.js,
	src/html/classic/ng/src/gmp/models/role.js,
	src/html/classic/ng/src/gmp/models/scanconfig.js,
	src/html/classic/ng/src/gmp/models/scanner.js,
	src/html/classic/ng/src/gmp/models/schedule.js,
	src/html/classic/ng/src/gmp/models/secinfo.js,
	src/html/classic/ng/src/gmp/models/tag.js,
	src/html/classic/ng/src/gmp/models/target.js,
	src/html/classic/ng/src/gmp/models/task.js,
	src/html/classic/ng/src/gmp/models/user.js,
	src/html/classic/ng/src/gmp/models/vulnerability.js: Introduce new entity_type
	property for model instances. With entity_type it will possible to generate
	links from entities without having to know the details of the current entity.
	Also update exports, parser imports, coding style and parsing of yes/no
	values. No model should use a type property directly anymore. Instead it
	should a property name like ${entity_type}_type e.g. scan_config_type.

