2017-07-03  Björn Ricks <bjoern.ricks@greenbone.net>

	* src/html/classic/ng/CMakeLists.txt,
	src/html/classic/ng/src/web/app.js,
	src/html/classic/ng/src/web/components/dashboard/dashboard.js,
	src/html/classic/ng/src/web/components/provider/cachefactoryprovider.js,
	src/html/classic/ng/src/web/components/provider/cacheprovider.js,
	src/html/classic/ng/src/web/entities/container.js,
	src/html/classic/ng/src/web/pages/assetspage.js,
	src/html/classic/ng/src/web/pages/homepage.js,
	src/html/classic/ng/src/web/pages/scanspage.js,
	src/html/classic/ng/src/web/pages/secinfopage.js,
	src/html/classic/ng/src/web/utils/withCache.js: Introduce
	CacheFactoryProvider, CacheProvider components and withCache HOC. They
	abstract and simplify the cache usage. The react docs highly recommend to not
	use the context api directly. With this change the context api usage is
	abstracted and we are able to change the details of the cache easier in
	future.

2017-07-03  Björn Ricks <bjoern.ricks@greenbone.net>

	* src/html/classic/ng/src/web/utils/render.js: Add helper function to render
	children. Until the next react release (react 16) it is not possible to return
	several react elements from a render function/method. Thererefore if a
	component encapsulates several sub components it must be wrapped in a div.

2017-07-03  Björn Ricks <bjoern.ricks@greenbone.net>

	* src/html/classic/ng/CMakeLists.txt,
	src/html/classic/ng/src/web/components/icon/icon.js,
	src/html/classic/ng/src/web/components/icon/withIconSize.js,
	src/html/classic/ng/src/web/components/provider/iconsizeprovider.js: Introduce
	IconSizeProvider component and withIconSize HOC. With these components it is
	possible to change the default icon size via react context.

