2017-06-12  Björn Ricks <bjoern.ricks@greenbone.net>

	* src/html/classic/ng/src/web/assetspage.js,
	src/html/classic/ng/src/web/homepage.js,
	src/html/classic/ng/src/web/scanspage.js,
	src/html/classic/ng/src/web/secinfopage.js: Add caches for the section
	dashboard pages.

2017-06-12  Björn Ricks <bjoern.ricks@greenbone.net>

	* src/html/classic/js/gsa_dashboard.js,
	src/html/classic/ng/src/gmp/cache.js: Update Cache classes to store cache
	entry instances. Allow to invalidate cache entries.

	* src/html/classic/ng/src/gmp/http.js: Update http client class to accept a
	cache object on each request instead of storing the cache itself. This
	introduces a more flexible caching approach where each request can be cached
	independently.

	* src/html/classic/ng/src/web/app.js: Instanciate a CacheFactory, pass it
	to all components via context and also pass it to the global gmp instance.
	With this change all caches can be inspected in the browser console via
	gmp.caches.

	* src/html/classic/ng/src/web/entities/container.js: Rework reloading of
	entities. Differentiate between filter set by the user and the loaded filter
	from the response. E.g. on the first request the user didn't set any filter.
	Therefore filter is undefined and loaded filter will be the default filter for
	the resource. For caching the http data will be stored with the url derived
	from the users filter and not from the loaded filter anymore. This results in
	less entries and more consistend data in the cache.
	Also with this change every entity page will get its own cache. This allows
	for marking all cache entries as dirty if e.g. data has been deleted. If the
	returned data from the cache is dirty it will be reloaded automatically.

2017-06-12  Björn Ricks <bjoern.ricks@greenbone.net>

	* src/html/classic/ng/src/gmp/gmp.js: Allow to pass a cache factory instance
	to the gmp instance.

2017-06-12  Björn Ricks <bjoern.ricks@greenbone.net>

	* src/html/classic/ng/src/web/proptypes.js: Add proptypes for cache and
	cachefactory instances.

2017-06-12  Björn Ricks <bjoern.ricks@greenbone.net>

	* src/html/classic/ng/src/gmp/cache.js: Introduce a CacheFactory class. This
	class is a key-value store for different cache objects.

2017-06-12  Björn Ricks <bjoern.ricks@greenbone.net>

	* src/html/classic/ng/src/gmp/cache.js: Introduce a cache entry class. This
	class will contain meta info about data in a cache. Currently if the cache
	data is dirty.

2017-06-12  Björn Ricks <bjoern.ricks@greenbone.net>

	* src/html/classic/ng/src/gmp/commands/users.js: Don't cache user settings by
	default.

2017-06-12  Björn Ricks <bjoern.ricks@greenbone.net>

	* src/html/classic/ng/src/web/sticky/sticky.js: Only set sticky css class if
	the element is sticky. This fixes displaying the small greenbone icon when the
	menu is sticked to the head of the page.

