2017-02-27  Björn Ricks <bjoern.ricks@greenbone.net>

	* src/html/classic/ng/CMakeLists.txt,
	src/html/classic/ng/src/gmp/collectionlist.js,
	src/html/classic/ng/src/gmp/command.js,
	src/html/classic/ng/src/gmp/commands/alerts.js,
	src/html/classic/ng/src/gmp/commands/certbund.js,
	src/html/classic/ng/src/gmp/commands/cpes.js,
	src/html/classic/ng/src/gmp/commands/credentials.js,
	src/html/classic/ng/src/gmp/commands/cves.js,
	src/html/classic/ng/src/gmp/commands/dfncert.js,
	src/html/classic/ng/src/gmp/commands/filters.js,
	src/html/classic/ng/src/gmp/commands/login.js,
	src/html/classic/ng/src/gmp/commands/notes.js,
	src/html/classic/ng/src/gmp/commands/nvt.js,
	src/html/classic/ng/src/gmp/commands/ovaldefs.js,
	src/html/classic/ng/src/gmp/commands/overrides.js,
	src/html/classic/ng/src/gmp/commands/portlists.js,
	src/html/classic/ng/src/gmp/commands/schedules.js,
	src/html/classic/ng/src/gmp/commands/secinfo.js,
	src/html/classic/ng/src/gmp/commands/targets.js,
	src/html/classic/ng/src/gmp/commands/tasks.js,
	src/html/classic/ng/src/gmp/commands/users.js,
	src/html/classic/ng/src/gmp/commands/wizard.js,
	src/html/classic/ng/src/gmp/http.js,
	src/html/classic/ng/src/gmp/parser.js,
	src/html/classic/ng/src/web/alerts/dialog.js,
	src/html/classic/ng/src/web/dashboard/dashboard.js,
	src/html/classic/ng/src/web/entities/container.js,
	src/html/classic/ng/src/web/page.js,
	src/html/classic/ng/src/web/reports/reportspage.js,
	src/html/classic/ng/src/web/targets/dialogcontainer.js,
	src/html/classic/ng/src/web/tasks/dialog.js,
	src/html/classic/ng/src/web/wizard/advancedtaskwizard.js,
	src/html/classic/ng/src/web/wizard/taskwizard.js: Heavy refactoring of the
	http response handling. We now always return a Response object for a http
	request. The Response object has two members: data and meta. The data can be
	an arbitrary js object (mostly a model instance). This depends on the command
	and its methods. Meta contains meta info about the response. It is always
	defined and an object. Currently it can be used e.g. to identify if a
	response is comming from the cache.

	If a command method returns a list a CollectionList is still returned instead
	of a Response object. But the CollectionList now also contains the meta
	object.

