2017-02-15 Björn Ricks <bjoern.ricks@greenbone.net>

	* src/html/classic/ng/CMakeLists.txt,
	src/html/classic/ng/src/web/credentials/dialog.js,
	src/html/classic/ng/src/web/credentials/dialog2.js,
	src/html/classic/ng/src/web/portlists/dialog.js,
	src/html/classic/ng/src/web/targets/dialog.js,
	src/html/classic/ng/src/web/targets/dialogcontainer.js,
	src/html/classic/ng/src/web/tasks/dialog.js: Refactor TargetDialog to use
	withDialog HOC. Introduce a TargetDialogContainer component that encapsulates
	most of the functionality of the old TargetDialog. The advantage of using this
	pattern is in separating the data from the presentation and at the end getting
	an easier reusability. This new approach uses composition instead of
	inheritance.

