	src/html/classic/ng/src/web/reports/table.js: Add reports page by using the
	new entities components.

2017-02-09 Björn Ricks <bjoern.ricks@greenbone.net>

	* src/html/classic/ng/CMakeLists.txt,
	src/html/classic/ng/src/web/entities/actions.js,
	src/html/classic/ng/src/web/entities/container.js,
	src/html/classic/ng/src/web/entities/page.js,
	src/html/classic/ng/src/web/entities/row.js,
	src/html/classic/ng/src/web/entities/table.js: Add new base components for
	entities list pages. These components will not use inheritence anymore.
	Instead composition with higher order components is used. This allows much
	more flexibility by sticking individual components together and moves (nearly)
	all state to the top. State information is passed down the component tree as
	properties. The downside of this approach is in more rendering cycles when
	state has changed.

2017-02-09 Björn Ricks <bjoern.ricks@greenbone.net>

	* src/html/classic/ng/src/web/render.js: Add helper function to render a
	component.

