2017-02-01 Björn Ricks <bjoern.ricks@greenbone.net>

	* src/html/classic/ng/CMakeLists.txt,
	src/html/classic/ng/src/web/entities/listpage.js,
	src/html/classic/ng/src/web/powerfilter/applyoverridesgroup.js,
	src/html/classic/ng/src/web/css/powerfilter.css,
	src/html/classic/ng/src/web/powerfilter/css/powerfilter.css,
	src/html/classic/ng/src/web/filterdialog.js,
	src/html/classic/ng/src/web/powerfilter/dialog.js,
	src/html/classic/ng/src/web/powerfilter/filterstringgroup.js,
	src/html/classic/ng/src/web/powerfilter/firstresultgroup.js,
	src/html/classic/ng/src/web/powerfilter/minqodgroup.js,
	src/html/classic/ng/src/web/powerfilter.js,
	src/html/classic/ng/src/web/powerfilter/powerfilter.js,
	src/html/classic/ng/src/web/powerfilter/resultsperpagegroup.js,
	src/html/classic/ng/src/web/powerfilter/sortbygroup.js,
	src/html/classic/ng/src/web/results/filterdialog.js,
	src/html/classic/ng/src/web/results/resultspage.js,
	src/html/classic/ng/src/web/tasks/filterdialog.js: Start to refactor
	filter edit dialogs. Implement a withFilterDialog higher order component which
	will replace the FilterDialog class at the end. As a first step the
	ResultsFilterDialog is converted to use this new withFilterDialog HOC.
	To be able to resuse as much as possible the old renderXyz methods of
	FilterDialog are extracted into own Components. Therefore the powerfilter
	related code is moved into a powerfilter sub directory.

