2016-12-16  Björn Ricks <bjoern.ricks@greenbone.net>

	* src/gsad_http.c, src/gsad_http.h: Introduce new
	handler_send_reauthentication function. This function handles displaying the
	login page dependend of using gsa ng and passing the xml parameter.
	If gsa ng is activated and a normal page is requested the user should be
	redirected to the ng login page. If the request is an api request
	(xml param is 1) then a 40X must be returned and a redirect most not occur.

	* src/gsad_http_handler.c: Call handler_send_reauthentication in
	handle_setup_user and handle_logout functions.

2016-12-16  Björn Ricks <bjoern.ricks@greenbone.net>

	* src/gsad.c (exec_omp_get): Remove duplicate asignment of ret value.

2016-12-16  Björn Ricks <bjoern.ricks@greenbone.net>

	* src/gsad.c (exec_omp_post): Cleanup function variables.

2016-12-16  Björn Ricks <bjoern.ricks@greenbone.net>

	Use dynamic memory allocation for cmd_response_data_t structs

	* src/gsad_cmd.c, src/gsad_cmd.h: Remove cmd_response_data_reset function.
	Change cmd_response_data_init to a static and therefore private function.

	* src/gsad_http_handler.c: Change handler_send_response function to always free
	cmd_response_data_t. Use pointers to cmd_response_data_t structs.

	* src/gsad_http.c: Allocate memory for cmd_response_data_t structs dynamically
	and use only functions to access cmd_response_data_t properties.

	* src/gsad.c: Use pointer to cmd_response_data_t in exec_omp_post and free it
	afterwards. Also use functions to access cmd_response_data_t properties.

2016-12-16  Björn Ricks <bjoern.ricks@greenbone.net>

	* src/gsad_cmd.c, src/gsad_cmd.h: Introduce cmd_response_data_new and
	cmd_response_data_free for dynamic cmd_response_data_t struct memory
	allocation.

