	file.

2016-12-12  Björn Ricks <bjoern.ricks@greenbone.net>

	Preperation for adding the Single Page Application based on react

	The single page application can be devided into two parts: First a javascript
	api for the gmp and second the actual web application based on react.

	* src/html/classic/ng/src/*.js: Common js files for gmp api and web
	application.

	* src/html/classic/ng/src/web: React web components building the new gsa
	single page app.

	* src/html/classic/ng/src/gmp: GMP JavaScript api files

	* src/html/classic/ng/public/index.html: HTML template for the main entry
	file.

	* src/html/classic/ng/public/config.js: Empty config. The config file can be
	used to set sever url and port for the ajax requests.

	* src/html/classic/ng/package.json: node package json file describing the
	js application, its dependencies and scripts.

