2016-12-06  Björn Ricks <bjoern.ricks@greenbone.net>

	Refactoring of http request handling and code splitting

	* src/gsad.c, src/gsad_http_handler.c, src/gsad_http_handler.h: Move http
	request handling from gsad.c to gsad_http.c. Remove a lot of duplicate code.
	Introduce a http_handler struct that acts like a chain of functions. Each
	function in the chain can be called to handle the current request. In the
	function it can be decided to create a response or leave the response for the
	next http_handler in the chain. Additionally it is possible to only pass some
	data to the following http_handlers in the chain.

2016-12-06  Björn Ricks <bjoern.ricks@greenbone.net>

	* src/gsad_http.c: Set content_type to application/xml in gsad_message if xml
	param is set. This fixes setting the content type for xml responses.

2016-12-06  Björn Ricks <bjoern.ricks@greenbone.net>

	* src/gsad_cmd.h: Add content_type to cmd_response_data_t. This allows to set
	the content type for commands.

	* src/gsad_cmd.c: Initalize content type of cmd_response_data_t with text/html.

2016-12-06  Björn Ricks <bjoern.ricks@greenbone.net>

	* src/gsad_base.h, src/gsad_content_type.h: Move content_type definition into
	a seperate header.

	* src/gsad_http.c, src/gsad_omp.c: Include gsad_base.h for xsl_transform and
	ctime_r_strip_newline functions.

	* src/gsad_http.h, src/gsad_omp.h: Include gsad_content_type.h.

2016-12-06  Björn Ricks <bjoern.ricks@greenbone.net>

	* src/gsad_http.c, src/gsad_http.h: Update coding style and add missing
	docstrings. Use content_type_t instead of enum content_type.

